Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: So, I've been sent the wrong product twice now. I ordered the AGV.

Speaker 1: Okay, what's your name and date of birth?

Speaker 2: JT France, 6-28-64.

Speaker 1: Thank you. Okay, so I am looking at your profile, JT.

Speaker 2: It looks like you do receive Viagra AGV, a quantity of 10 pills.

Speaker 2: Both times.

Speaker 1: Oh.

Speaker 1: Do you have the pills with you?

Speaker 2: I do. I'm looking at the bottle right now.

Speaker 2: And the easiest way to make sure that you got the AGV is by taking a look at the capsules.

Speaker 1: They should have the number 50 engraved on them. Can you verify that for me?

Speaker 2: It's 3-3-9.

Speaker 1: Okay, yes. It looks like they did send you the classic Viagra and not the AGV.

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: So, don't worry about it. I'll notify the pharmacy so that they reship the correct order to you, okay?

Speaker 2: And then they should be sending you a quantity of 20 this time to make up for the previous order too, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay. Yeah, these are white.

Speaker 2: Yeah, they're supposed to be white. They're not going to be blue.

Speaker 1: Actually, the blue dye is bad for you, so we don't do them blue.

Speaker 2: Okay, so the AGV will be white also?

Speaker 1: It will be white, yes. But the reason, the way you'll be able to identify that it's the AGV,

Speaker 2: it's because it will say Greenstone LLC on the label.

Speaker 1: And then every single pill will have the number 50 engraved on the tablet.

Speaker 2: Okay, gotcha.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: All right, thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay, you're welcome. Have a good day. Bye.

Speaker 2: Thank you, ma'am. Bye.
